Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. _____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION memorializing
2 Corporal Blake Reynolds.
3 Whereas, Blake Adair Reynolds, 31, of Muncie, Indiana,
4 finished his earthly watch on November 12, 2025, after giving
5 his life in the line of duty while serving the Delaware County
6 Sheriff's Office;
7 Whereas, Born July 20, 1994, in Muncie, Blake lived his life
8 rooted in faith, family, and service;
9 Whereas, Blake graduated from Delta High School in 2013
10 and graduated from Ball State University with a bachelor's
11 degree in Criminal Justice;
12 Whereas, Blake proudly served with the Delaware County
13 Sheriff's Office for three years, most recently with the rank of
14 Corporal;
15 Whereas, From his first day on the job, Deputy Reynolds
16 knew law enforcement wasn't just his profession, it was his
17 calling, as he was hardwired to protect and serve with courage,
18 compassion, and a heart for people;
19 Whereas, Blake's faith in Jesus Christ shaped everything
20 about him, as he loved deeply, gave freely, lived with quiet
21 conviction, and was the kind of person who could both make
22 you laugh when you needed it most and stand firm when life felt
23 heavy;
2026 RC 1515/DI JR

2
1 Whereas, Outside of work, Blake found joy in the simple
2 things, such as snuggling with his sidekick kitten, Nightwing,
3 listening to his favorite head-banging music, watching scary
4 movies, diving into history books, quoting Star Wars, and
5 cheering for Batman as if it were real life;
6 Whereas, Deputy Reynolds is survived by his wife, Allison
7 (Eddleman) Reynolds, his parents, Bruce and Melissa (Adair)
8 Reynolds, his brother, Dustin Reynolds, his maternal
9 grandparents, Calvin and Sandra Adair, as well as his paternal
10 grandparents, Bruce and Linda Reynolds and Cora and Barry
11 Bryans; and
12 Whereas, Deputy Reynolds will be missed by his friends
13 and family, who remember him for his faith, his loyalty, and his
14 service to his community, paying the ultimate sacrifice in the
15 line of duty: Therefore,
16 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly
17 of the State of Indiana, the House of Representatives
18 concurring:
19 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly
20 memorializes Deputy Blake Reynolds and honors his service to
21 the citizens of Indiana.
22 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
23 to transmit copies of this Resolution to the family of Deputy
24 Reynolds.
2026 RC 1515/DI JR

